At the February 13, 2019 meeting of the District School Board of Madison County a Memorandum of Agreement
(MOU) with the Madison County Education Association (MCEA) was approved by the Board for two (2) employee furlough days. The MOU was ratified by 91% of instructional employees and 92% of non-instructional employees. The following changes will be made to the school calendar:
1. April 11, 2019 will be a full day of school instead of
an early release day;
2. March 8, 2019 will be an employee furlough day -
non-attendance day for both students & staff;
3. May 23, 2019 will be the last day of school for
students;
4. May 24, 2019 will be a non-working furlough day for
staff.

